questions.question_text_1: Suppose you conduct a chi-squared test of independence on the categorical variables cities and brand preferences at the significance level 0.05. You obtain a p-value of 0.07. What will you conclude?
question_texts: Suppose you conduct a chi-squared test of independence on the categorical variables cities and brand preferences at the significance level 0.05. You obtain a p-value of 0.07. What will you conclude?

options.option_text: Reject the null hypothesis and conclude that the categorical variables areindependent
Reject the null hypothesis and conclude that the categorical variables are notindependent
Fail to reject the null hypothesis and conclude that the categorical variables areindependent
Fail to reject the null hypothesis and conclude that the categorical variables arenot independent

questions.question_text_1: There are 4 business units. Using the DEA, you solve the LP for all the four business units and find the efficiencies for these units. The efficiency is denoted by E. For these units, E1 = 0.83, E2 = 1, E3 = 0.57, E4 = 0.91. Which of these units are efficient?

questions.question_text_1: You solve the primal of a linear program with maximization objective, three decision variables and two constraints of the less than or equal to type. Non-negativity restrictions apply on the decision variables. After solving the linear program, you find that the first constraint is binding (lhs = rhs) and the second constraint is not binding (lhs < rhs). Which of the following statements are correct?
question_texts: You solve the primal of a linear program with maximization objective, three decision variables and two constraints of the less than or equal to type. Non-negativity restrictions apply on the decision variables. After solving the linear program, you find that the first constraint is binding (lhs = rhs) and the second constraint is not binding (lhs < rhs). Which of the following statements are correct?

options.option_text: There are two decision variables in the dual
The dual variable corresponding to the second constraint is zero
There are three decision variables in the dual
The dual variable corresponding to the first constraint is zero
